{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WQSj7T8LeXdRzct3XK2Qcm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Autonomous Dev Progress Log\n     2→\n     3→Each entry is appended by the autonomous agent after completing work.\n     4→\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→## 2026-03-18 — Run 1\n     8→\n     9→### What was done\n    10→\n    11→**1. valueSortify — Critical security fix (PR #9, merged)**\n    12→- Upgraded jspdf from v2.5.2 to v4.2.1 and jspdf-autotable from v3.8.4 to v5.0.7\n    13→- Fixed 3 vulnerabilities: prototype pollution (critical), ReDoS bypass (high), XSS via dompurify (moderate)\n    14→- Updated `ResultsPhase.jsx` to use the new `applyPlugin()` API required by jspdf-autotable v5\n    15→- Build verified, 0 vulnerabilities remaining\n    16→\n    17→**2. groceryGenius — npm audit fix (PR #34, merged)**\n    18→- Applied `npm audit fix` to resolve 8 of 16 security findings (non-breaking updates)\n    19→- Fixed: undici HTTP smuggling (high), glob command injection (high), minimatch ReDoS (high), rollup path traversal (high), qs DoS, lodash prototype pollution, on-headers manipulation, brace-expansion ReDoS\n    20→- Remaining 8 moderate esbuild findings are dev-only transitive deps via drizzle-kit\n    21→\n    22→**3. job-scraper — Unit test suite (PR #8, merged)**\n    23→- Added 59 unit tests using Node's built-in `node:test` runner (zero new dependencies)\n    24→- Covers all 3 ATS adapters: Greenhouse, Ashby, Lever (URL parsing, salary extraction, requirements extraction)\n    25→- Tests base adapter infrastructure: DomainRateLimiter, error classes, Zod schema validation\n    26→- Exported previously-private pure helper functions to enable direct testing\n    27→- Added `npm test` script to package.json\n    28→\n    29→### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n    30→- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n    31→- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n    32→- **waymo-sim**: Bug in `entity.py` line 123 — hardcoded `0.1` divisor in waypoint interpolation P-controller instead of actual `dt`. `world.py reset()` doesn't restore entity positions.\n    33→- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug.\n    34→- **runCoach**: Empty repo — only README and LICENSE.\n    35→\n    36→---\n    37→\n    38→## 2026-03-18 — Run 2\n    39→\n    40→### What was done\n    41→\n    42→**waymo-sim — Two engine bug fixes (PR #8, merged)**\n    43→- Fixed hardcoded `0.1` divisor in `entity.py:interpolate_waypoint()` P-controller. The acceleration calculation now uses the actual `dt` parameter passed from the world engine, so NPC vehicles follow waypoints correctly at any timestep size.\n    44→- Fixed `world.py:reset()` to restore entity positions, headings, and speeds to their initial values. Previously it only cleared collision flags, leaving entities at their last simulated positions.\n    45→- Added 2 regression tests covering both bugs (28/28 tests pass).\n    46→\n    47→### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n    48→- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n    49→- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n    50→- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GSm9cZNgmq36kHkCEFtxYs","session_id":"536c0e0f-d624-40db-b42c-9dee9b307f61","uuid":"d854dcfb-ea04-46ab-a09a-ef197c181e07","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:00:47.013Z"}
