{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q3P6ZfuzA8BjeW7K5FkHhW","type":"tool_result","content":"   951→  - `claude.test.ts` (22 tests): text/string/array content extraction, content field priority (text > content), role mapping (human→user, assistant passthrough, missing→user), non-text content part filtering, edge cases (empty messages, no sender, multiple conversations)\n   952→  - `gemini.test.ts` (24 tests): all 3 format variations (Takeout flat array, AI Studio conversation array, single conversation object), multi-part message joining, content fallback field, role mapping (model→assistant), createTime propagation, empty parts skipping\n   953→  - `processor.test.ts` (10 tests): detectProvider auto-detection across all formats, priority ordering (chatgpt before gemini for ambiguous title+messages), invalid/empty input handling\n   954→- 129 total tests (was 53), all passing, build verified\n   955→- Deployed to staging — app running (308 redirect to auth)\n   956→\n   957→### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n   958→- **runeval**: 129 tests now. Remaining untested: crypto.ts, auth/tokens.ts, auth/refresh.ts, email.ts, logger.ts, openai.ts, garmin/adapter.ts (all require mocking external deps)\n   959→- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n   960→\n   961→---\n   962→\n   963→## 2026-03-20 — Run 40\n   964→\n   965→### What was done\n   966→\n   967→**groceryGenius — WCAG accessibility attributes for interactive components (PR #57, auto-merged)**\n   968→- Added `aria-label` to 4 Radix UI sliders in `location-preferences.tsx` with dynamic current-value text (store radius, price/time/distance weights)\n   969→- Added `role=\"button\"`, `tabIndex={0}`, and `aria-label` to drag handle in `shopping-list.tsx` so screen readers announce \"Drag to reorder {item}\"\n   970→- Added `aria-label` to icon-only remove buttons (X) and add button (Plus) in `shoppin